<section class="section ai-without-specs" id="ai-without-specs">
	<div class="container-narrow">
		<div class="section-header">
			<h2>The Problem: AI Without Specs</h2>
			<p class="section-subtitle">
				AI coding tools are powerful, but without clear direction, they amplify problems instead of solving them.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="problems-list">
			<div class="problem-card">
				<div class="problem-header">
					<div class="problem-icon">üé≤</div>
					<h3>Unpredictable Outputs</h3>
				</div>
				<div class="problem-content">
					<p class="problem-desc"><strong>Problem:</strong> Vague prompts lead to inconsistent implementations. AI guesses at requirements and edge cases.</p>
					<p class="solution-desc"><strong>Solution:</strong> Specs define exact requirements and constraints. AI builds what you <em>actually</em> need.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="problem-card">
				<div class="problem-header">
					<div class="problem-icon">üîÅ</div>
					<h3>Endless Iteration Loops</h3>
				</div>
				<div class="problem-content">
					<p class="problem-desc"><strong>Problem:</strong> Without upfront clarity, you're constantly reworking code instead of shipping.</p>
					<p class="solution-desc"><strong>Solution:</strong> Changes become intentional updates to the spec, not ad-hoc code rewrites.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="problem-card">
				<div class="problem-header">
					<div class="problem-icon">üß©</div>
					<h3>Integration Nightmares</h3>
				</div>
				<div class="problem-content">
					<p class="problem-desc"><strong>Problem:</strong> AI generates components that don't fit together. Incompatible patterns, duplicated logic.</p>
					<p class="solution-desc"><strong>Solution:</strong> Design phase establishes architecture. Every component knows its place in the system.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="problem-card">
				<div class="problem-header">
					<div class="problem-icon">‚ö†Ô∏è</div>
					<h3>Missing Edge Cases</h3>
				</div>
				<div class="problem-content">
					<p class="problem-desc"><strong>Problem:</strong> AI focuses on happy paths. Error handling and accessibility get overlooked until production.</p>
					<p class="solution-desc"><strong>Solution:</strong> Requirements phase identifies edge cases upfront. AI implements complete, production-ready features.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="callout">
			<h4>Bottom Line</h4>
			<p>AI is a multiplier, not a replacement for thinking. Give it clear specs, and it becomes your most productive teammate.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

